<subSubSection id="C31265792157FFFAFF221F66FEE0FB99" box="[151,382,1123,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF221F66FEE0FB99" blockId="5.[151,794,1086,1149]" box="[151,382,1123,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
(
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFF2A1F66FEBBFB99" box="[159,293,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Figs. 1C–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE851F66FEE8FB99" box="[304,374,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">3A–D</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792157FFFAFF221FA1FE98FA72" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF221FA1FE98FA72" blockId="5.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF221FA1FE8FFB5A" bold="true" box="[151,273,1188,1214]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF221FA1FE94FB5A" bold="true" box="[151,266,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B172157FFFAFEC01FA1FE54FB5B" box="[373,458,1188,1215]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
. Width 
<quantity id="4CF09B172157FFFAFD901FA1FD1FFB5B" box="[549,641,1188,1215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" unit="mm" value="9.1">9.1 mm</quantity>
. Dorsal surface green, punctures black on dark brown spots forming irregular lines (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFEFF1FCDFE3BFB06" box="[330,421,1224,1250]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Beneath green with two lateral stripes of dense, black punctures; evaporatorium dark brown (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFF451FE9FED5FAE2" box="[240,331,1260,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Humeral angles projection short, dentiform. Antennae and legs yellowish-green. Costal margin of corium and hypocostal ridge with punctures on dark spots. Posterolateral angles of pygophore developed; dorsal rim and most of the genital cup black (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFDEC1E31FD4BFAAA" box="[601,725,1332,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3B–C</figureCitation>
). Genital cup excavated close to ventral rim; parameres short, claw-like (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFEBA1E5DFEF9FA96" box="[271,359,1368,1394]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Genital plates irregularly punctured, punctures on black spots. Valvifers 8 strongly acuminated (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFF151E79FF64FA72" box="[160,250,1404,1430]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792157FFFAFF721EA5FBDDF81F" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF721EA5FC4CF976" blockId="5.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF721EA5FED3FA5E" bold="true" box="[199,333,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Description</emphasis>
. Head wider than long (1.5 times). Forth and part of the third rostral segments laying on metasternal process anterior bifurcation. Thorax: Pronotum wider than long (2.7 times); cicatrices not delimited by grooves, with rows of black punctures forming irregular lines. Thoracic segments densely and irregularly punctured, punctures in black spots. Evaporatorium with black spots below outer translucent layer; lateral area semicircular, punctures on black spots. Metasternal process green; anterior bifurcation with arms strongly acuminate; distally with a few dark spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFF541D51FEA2F98A" box="[225,316,1620,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Abdomen: connexivum densely punctuated, punctures black (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFBBE1D51FBFCF98A" box="[1035,1122,1620,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); segments III–VI medially with a callus. One trichobothrium in line and other lateral to the spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF721D9EFBF3F88E" blockId="5.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF721D9EFE9CF952" bold="true" box="[199,258,1691,1718]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFEA11D99FE0DF952" box="[276,403,1692,1718]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3A–C</figureCitation>
). Pygophore greenish-yellow, elongated (1.1x longer than wide). Dorsal rim rounded, not projected over the genital cup (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE461DC5FDD3F93E" box="[499,589,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Diaphragm back to parameres dark green (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFB8A1DC5FB09F93E" box="[1087,1175,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Superior processes of the genital cup small, reniform, gently excavated, touching the dorsal rim. Parameres dark yellow, contrasting with the mostly black genital cup; laterally compressed. Proctiger light brown, elongated (1.4 times), wider ventrally; laterally slightly excavated (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE6F1C29FDAAF8A2" box="[474,564,1836,1862]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim in an open “V” (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFC261C29FC73F8A2" box="[915,1005,1836,1862]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); expansions not projected but tumid. Ventral surface irregularly punctured on distal third, punctures on black spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFBBD1C55FBFEF88E" box="[1032,1120,1872,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF721C76FBDDF81F" blockId="5.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF721C76FE80F86A" bold="true" box="[199,286,1907,1934]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE841C71FE11F86A" box="[305,399,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[161,1435,531,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[151,1435,525,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Genitalia of G. nigricava sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500677/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 wider than long (1.2 times); distal margin strongly acuminate and projected posteriorly exceeding valvifer 9. Valvulae 8 medially elevated, visible among valvifers 8. Valvifer 9 longer than wide (1.2 times), partially covered laterally by valvifers 8. Laterotergites 8 longer than wide (1.3 times), exceeding laterotergites 9. Laterotergites 9 flattened almost level with abdominal segment VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792154FFF9FF721B93FD64FF32" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22154FFF9FF721B93FD64FF32" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02154FFF9FF721B93FED7FF55" bold="true" box="[199,329,150,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02154FFF9FF721B93FEDCFF55" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The name refers to posterolateral angles of the pygophore black and deeply excavated. From the Latin. 
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02154FFF9FF551BBEFEA8FF30" box="[224,310,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Nigrum</emphasis>
(black or dark) and 
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02154FFF9FDAF1BBEFDFEFF31" box="[538,608,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Cavus</emphasis>
(excavation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792154FFF9FF721BDAFD4CFE36" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22154FFF9FF721BDAFCC5FEF9" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02154FFF9FF721BDAFED7FF1D" bold="true" box="[199,329,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02154FFF9FF721BDAFEDCFF1D" bold="true" box="[199,322,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species is distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712154FFF9FCB91BDAFC32FF1D" authorityName="Correia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2016" box="[780,940,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02154FFF9FCB91BDAFC32FF1D" box="[780,940,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Grammedessa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its posterolateral angles of the pygophore deeply excavated and black, and by its parameres claw-shaped.
</paragraph>
